Boil a large #pot of water for the corn and pre-heat your #oven to 220 degrees. Remove the core from each @yellow pepper{1} and @red pepper{1} and cut into chunky slices. Chop up the @coriander{3%sprigs} and finely chop the @red onion{1}(finely chopped). Lastly, drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1}.

Place the @corn on the cob{2} in your gently boiling water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for ~{7%minutes}. Afterwards, drain your corn and leave it to the side for later.

Whilst your corn cooks, coat your pepper in a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Put on a #baking tray{} and place in your #oven for ~{20%minutes}, or until they're soft and a little crispy around the edges.

Cook your red onion in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-low heat with a splash of @olive oil{1%splash}. After ~{5%minutes} add in the mixed beans, @habanero sauce{1%tbsp}, @cumin{1%tsp}, @tomato puree{1%tsp} and a glug of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Cook with a #lid on for ~{15%minutes}.

Coat your corn in the @chipotle paste{1%tbsp}, the zest and juice of the @lime{1} and a dash of @olive oil{}. Roll your corn in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} to coat it. Turn your #grill to high heat.

> Tip: If your oven and grill are combined, move your peppers down to keep warm.

Put your corn on another baking tray under your #grill and cook it until it's nicely browned.

== Refried Beans ==

Now to make your refried beans! Take out two-thirds of your bean mixture and mash up to a paste using the back of a #fork. Now add your remaining whole beans into your mashed beans with half of your coriander. Check for seasoning and add some @salt if necessary.

== Avocado ==

Cut lengthways into the @avocado{1} and when you reach the stone, turn your #knife around it to cut the avocado into two, neat halves. Pull the avocado apart, remove the stone and then slide a #knife around the flesh to release it. Now slice the flesh lengthways.

== To Serve ==

To serve, simply place your corn on top of your refried beans. Mix your roasted peppers with your avocado and your remaining coriander and serve this on the side. Ándale!